PART 1 — SUSTAINABLE USE LICENSE (applies to Multi-Head Additions)
================================================================================

This software includes original work ("Multi-Head Additions") written by the
copyright holder and distributed under the terms below.

1. GRANT OF RIGHTS

   Subject to the conditions in Section 2, the copyright holder grants you a
   non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free license to use, copy, modify, and
   distribute the Multi-Head Additions solely for your internal business
   purposes or personal use.

   You may also deploy the software for your own organization's internal use
   or for providing services to your direct clients, provided such use complies
   with the restrictions in Section 2.

2. CONDITIONS

   a. FREE USE TIER (SMALL & GROWING ORGANIZATIONS)
      If your organization's Annual Recurring Revenue (ARR) directly
      attributable to any product or service that incorporates or relies on the
      Multi-Head Additions is less than USD $2,000,000 in the most recent
      12-month period, you may use the Multi-Head Additions at no charge.

   b. COMMERCIAL LICENSE REQUIRED
      If your ARR from products or services using the Multi-Head Additions
      reaches or exceeds USD $2,000,000, you must obtain a paid commercial
      license within 90 days of crossing the threshold to continue using the
      Multi-Head Additions in production.
      Contact: nautilux2@gmail.com

   c. RESTRICTED USES (MANAGED / HOSTED SERVICES)
      You may not offer the Multi-Head Additions (or any software whose primary
      functionality or value is substantially derived from the Multi-Head
      Additions) as a hosted, managed, or SaaS service to third parties in a
      way that competes with the licensor's own offerings, without a separate
      written commercial agreement.

      This restriction does not prohibit:
        - Running the software internally for your own business operations.
        - Providing consulting, customization, or support services related to
          the software.
        - Hosting the software solely for your direct paying clients on
          infrastructure you control (as long as the Multi-Head features are
          not the core paid offering being resold).

   d. ATTRIBUTION
      You must retain all copyright, license, and attribution notices in any
      copy or substantial portion of the Multi-Head Additions.

   e. COMPLIANCE & REPORTING
      Upon reasonable written request (not more than once per year), you agree
      to provide a good-faith statement confirming your ARR status and
      compliance with this license.

3. DEFINITIONS

   "Multi-Head Additions" means the source code files added by the copyright
   holder that are not part of the upstream Supabase Studio project, including
   but not limited to: multi-head cluster management, license gating,
   self-hosted project creation, failover management, and the smh CLI.

   "Annual Recurring Revenue (ARR)" means the recurring revenue (subscription
   or usage-based) recognized in the most recent 12-month period that is
   directly generated from products or services incorporating the Multi-Head
   Additions. Revenue from unrelated business lines is not counted.

   "Substantially derived" refers to any product or service where the
   Multi-Head Additions (or their core functionality) provide the majority of
   the technical value or competitive advantage being offered to end users.

4. DISCLAIMER

   THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
   IMPLIED. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE COPYRIGHT HOLDER BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM,
   DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY ARISING FROM THE USE OF THE SOFTWARE.

